Rating: 4
Excellent! Plan ahead and prepare what you can ahead. Making the sauce ahead allows the flavors to enfuse the sauce. For those of you who wish to thicken the sauce, I might suggest potato starch instead of corn starch or 1/2 teaspoon of flour well mixed with butter to form a chick pea-sized ball. These won't leave the taste of cornstarch in your sauce and have less risk of lumping your sauce. I followed the instructions amost to a T and it turned out perfectly. As I didnt hve any port, I used sherry. The salt brining was a surprise! It didn't make the meat too salty and it was THE most tender meat I have EVER enjoyed. I will serve it with a yorkshire pudding next time. Thanks for sharing this wonderful recipe!

