I am the one who asked about making it the day before - no need to. This is the most amazing beef dish I have ever had for, taste, ease of prep, presentation you name it. And, I am not much of a beef eater but I couldn`t stop eating this one. Okay, brine up to two days is fine, that is what I did. I left it out of the fridge 3 hours sitting on the counter in a cool kitchen. I cooked it a bit longer as I do not care for rare - to 140 degrees and it was still very red. The port sauce while good, was a little too sweet for me, perhaps I will use a different port next time. I waited 20 minutes to slice into 1/2 inch slices and it was still very warm. You could not get anything as easy and as elegant as this dish. Mind you it is pricey, but because it is quite rich (all meat no fat) a little goes a long way. Costco is your best bet and the fact that our local culinary school purchases their meat from Costco says something. If you are buying from Costco, purchase the one that is trimmed and all the same thickness, it is shorter in length. Dry aging and salting are the key to the flavor.

