This is delicious! I let the meat brine for 22 hours and stuffed the tenderloin with pan roasted sliced garlic for the last eight hours. Roasting the garlic mellows its flavor. (roast the whole cloves with the skin on in a dry pan over medium-high heat until dark spots appear. Skin and slice, removing any burnt spots). Also, to mellow and enrich the flavor of the rub, I combined the cracked pepper and oil and simmered it over medium-low heat until the pepper was aromatic (6-10 mins) and then rubbed it over the meat. I used 3TBS of pepper and 3TBS of oil for abut 4.5 lbs of meat. For the sauce I used 3 1/2 cups of Kithcen Basics boxed beef stock (not broth) and the sauce turned out great, although the sauce took about an hour to reduce and the cognac took about 4-5 minutes to evaporate. The meat was tender and delicious. I served with roast broccoli, sauteed mushrooms, and smashed red potatoes, accompanied by 2002 BV Tapestry and 2001 Robert Craig Mt. Veeder Cab. The meal was a runaway hit!

