I agree, this recipe is delicious. However I must comment on the roasting temperature of 425 for the entire cook time. I was pretty surprised that the recipe called for this high of temperature the entire time. Needless to say about 1/2 way through the cooking time, I opened the oven to have smoke billowing out and my smoke alarm going off in front of my guests. It was just TOO hot and some of the juices were beginning to smoke. I then adjusted the oven temperature down to 375 and cooked until medium rare. I would recommend putting the tenderloin in for 15-20 minutes at 425 to seal in the juices and then drop the temperature to 375 to avoid the embarrassment of "burning" such a beautiful piece of meat! (FYI - I was cooking in Roast Mode in a Bosch Range)

